abstract: Peterson Institute for International Economics study says wide-ranging trade pact among dozen Pacific Rim nations will increase incomes, exports and growth in United States; says overall employment is not likely to increase.
snippet: An independent analysis of the trade deal suggested that displacement of workers in industries most vulnerable to competition would be relatively small....

headline.main: Trans-Pacific Trade Pact Would Lift U.S. Incomes, but Not Jobs Overall, Study Says
headline.print_headline: Wide-Ranging Trade Pact Would Lift American Incomes, Study Says
